# PrintExpress Technical Stack & Hosting Plan

This document outlines the current technical architecture of the PrintExpress application and provides a strategic plan for hosting it on Hostinger.

## Technical Stack Summary

### Frontend (Client)
- **Framework**: React 19 (Modern, component-based UI)
- **Build Tool**: Vite (Fast development and optimized builds)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 (Utility-first CSS framework)
- **Routing**: React Router DOM (Single Page Application routing)
- **API Client**: Axios (Promise-based HTTP requests)
- **Utilities**: 
  - `pdf-lib`: For PDF document generation and modification.
  - `react-hot-toast`: For smooth, non-intrusive notifications.

### Backend (Server)
- **Runtime**: Node.js (High-performance Javascript runtime)
- **Framework**: Express.js (Minimal and flexible web application framework)
- **Database ODM**: Mongoose (Elegant MongoDB object modeling)
- **Authentication**: JWT (JSON Web Tokens) & Bcryptjs (Password hashing)
- **File Handling**: Multer (Middleware for handling `multipart/form-data`)
- **Payment Gateway**: Stripe (Secure payment processing)

### Infrastructure & Services
- **Database**: MongoDB (Atlas Cloud recommended)
- **Cloud Storage**: Cloudinary (Image and file asset management)
- **Email/Notifications**: Configurable via environment variables.

